  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "22-27. I would also hear—\"should like to hear.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the man myself—No doubt Paul was fight when he said, \"The king knoweth of these things … for I am persuaded that none of these things are hidden from him; for this thing was not done in a corner\" (Ac 26:26). Hence his curiosity to see and hear the man who had raised such commotion and was remodelling to such an extent the whole Jewish life.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
